Refrain
God grant me an open mind and heart
to sing you praises through the day.

Verse 1

Let me be merciful, slow to judge,
Abiding in your love for all;
Grant me wisdom, a quiet tongue,
A humble Spirit, but standing tall.

Verse 2

The many words we do hear,
Tend to be forgotten through the year,
Let the Word you speak today,
Remain in my heart and mind
Throughout the day.

Verse 3

We are one people in your sight,
A common faith and sense of right,
We have been chosen by You
To life eternal and a world that's new, so

